1 2. “Eligible Guard member” means a current member of the
2 Oklahoma National Guard in good standing who has a high school
3 diploma or who has completed General Educational Development (GED)
4 requirements and who has enrolled in a technology center school; and
5 3. “Program” means the Oklahoma National Guard CareerTech
6 Assistance Program established pursuant to the provisions of this
7 section.
8 C. 1. There is hereby created the Oklahoma National Guard
9 CareerTech Assistance Program to provide assistance to eligible
10 Guard members who enroll in a technology center school. Subject to
11 the availability of funds, the amount of assistance shall be
12 equivalent to the amount of tuition for a career and technology
13 program in which the eligible Guard member is enrolled leading to
14 certification or licensure, not to exceed a maximum of three (3)
15 years.
16 2. Assistance provided pursuant to this section shall be
17 granted without any limitation other than the amount of funds
18 available for the program and the number of eligible Guard members
19 who apply, subject to any cap established by the Military Department
20 of the State of Oklahoma.
21 3. Assistance allowed by this section shall not be allowed for
22 courses taken in excess of the requirements for completion of a
23 technology center school program leading to certification or
24 licensure.
SB31 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 D. Assistance provided pursuant to this section shall be
2 allocated to the technology center school from the Oklahoma National
3 Guard CareerTech Assistance Revolving Fund created pursuant to
4 Section 2 of this act.
5 E. To be eligible to apply for the program, an eligible Guard
6 member shall:
7 1. Have at least one (1) year remaining on his or her
8 enlistment contract at the beginning of any semester for which the
9 member applies for assistance pursuant to this section;
10 2. Agree in writing to complete his or her current service
11 obligation in the Oklahoma National Guard; and
12 3. Agree in writing to serve actively in good standing with the
13 Oklahoma National Guard for not less than twenty-four (24) months
14 after completion of the last semester for which the member receives
15 assistance pursuant to this section.
16 F. To retain eligibility for the program, an eligible Guard
17 member shall:
18 1. Maintain good academic standing and satisfactory progress
19 according to standards of the technology center school in which the
20 member is enrolled;
21 2. Maintain the requirements for retention and completion as
22 established by the technology center school in which the member is
23 enrolled;
24
